rComments: He's a good prof, but the course is content-heavy. There are a lot of small details to study in addition to the bigger pictures. Midterm was a breeze. Final was much harder. But he does a decent bell curve at the end, as promised. Really only took this course so that I can take CHMC16 in the winter. Down side: final is worth 70%.
Great Prof., best in Chem, really cares about his students
Not very consistent with his office hours. Not very consistent with who gets selected for research credits.
Great Professor, tries his best to explain things well. I want to take more classes with him in the future

The Prof made the course interesting and gave us practical examples. The lecture notes were awesome and weren't just taken from the textbook. Exams and assignments were tough but fair. Great prof and good course!
